  "text": "Found 3 source files in sg-evals/expressjs-express that reference the deprecated req.host property specifically. In lib/request.js, req.host is defined as a deprecated getter using defineGetter that delegates to req.hostname with the deprecation message 'req.host: Use req.hostname instead'. The file test/req.host.js contains 11 test cases that exercise the deprecated req.host property directly (including IPv6, subdomains, X-Forwarded-Host, and trust proxy scenarios). History.md documents the deprecation in the 4.3.0 changelog entry: 'deprecate req.host -- use req.hostname instead' alongside the addition of req.hostname. Note: req.host is a substring of req.hostname — many other files reference req.hostname but NOT the deprecated req.host property. For example, test/req.hostname.js tests only the current req.hostname.",
